    AI Overview
    You can find many videos about keeping the world clean on YouTube, with topics ranging from children's educational content on recycling to short films about environmental change, and TED talks on environmental action. The UN Environment Programme also has videos on its YouTube channel. You can also find educational content on other platforms like Storyblocks for clean earth and environmental technology concepts. 
    Where to find videos on keeping the world clean:
    • YouTube:
      A vast platform with various channels and creators offering videos on this topic. 
      • National Geographic: often features documentaries and short films about environmental issues and solutions. 
      • Educational channels: like The Brain for Kids and Turtle Diary (Brain Star) have videos explaining how to care for the environment, particularly for children. 
      • TEDx Talks: such as Bella Lawson's on "Take Action to Keep the Earth Clean" provide inspiring messages. 
      • The UN Environment Programme offers videos and can be found by searching their YouTube channel. 
      • You can find channels that specifically create videos about Clean Earth Clubs and the importance of keeping school campuses litter-free. 
    • Storyblocks:
      Provides clean earth stock footage for various projects related to environmental technology and sustainable development goals.

    Types of videos you might find:
    • Environmental documentaries:
      Short films and feature-length documentaries that show the impact of human activity on the environment. 
    • Educational videos for kids:
      Animated and interactive videos that teach children about reducing, reusing, and recycling. 
    • Inspirational and action-oriented content:
      TED Talks and other videos that encourage viewers to take personal action to protect the environment. 
    • How-to guides:
      Videos offering practical tips on saving water, conserving energy, and properly disposing of waste. 
    • Stock footage:
      Professional video clips illustrating clean environments, nature, and sustainable practices.
